dict.string: Gauteng Wellbeing Mapper Beta uses your location to track where you spend time so you can map your activity spaces and compare them to your wellbeing responses. This beta version includes experimental features for testing.

Gauteng Wellbeing Mapper Beta accesses your motion data to improve location tracking of your activity spaces. This beta version includes experimental features for testing. The motion and location data it collects does not leave your phone unless you choose to share it by participating in beta testing or by exporting it manually.
Gauteng Wellbeing Mapper Beta uses your camera to make it possible for you to join research projects and test beta features by scanning QR codes.
Gauteng Wellbeing Mapper Beta sends you periodic reminders to participate in research surveys and test new features. These notifications help improve research participation and beta testing.
Gauteng Wellbeing Mapper Beta may access your photo library to attach images to survey responses or export data visualizations during beta testing.
